<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-85] If an error occurs inside a &quot;switch&quot; mediator the error is not captured through the onError sequence specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-85</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When an error is occurred in a switch mediator, the error is not returned properly through an onError sequence defined. Below is the configuration used.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;definitions xmlns=&quot;http://ws.apache.org/ns/synapse&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;endpoint name=&quot;division_epr&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;address uri=&quot;http://localhost:9001/axis2/services/Division&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;enableAddressing/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/address&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;localEntry key=&quot;div_request&quot;  src=&quot;file:repository/conf/sample/resources/transform/div_request.xslt&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;sequence name=&quot;fault&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;log level=&quot;full&quot; separator=&quot;,&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;property name=&quot;Error_prop&quot; value=&quot;Error Occurred&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/log&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/sequence&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;sequence name=&quot;main&quot; onError=&quot;fault&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;address uri=&quot;http://localhost:9001/axis2/services/Division&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;switch xmlns:ns1=&quot;http://div.math.com/xsd&quot; source=&quot;//ns1:return&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;case regex=&quot;2&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;xslt key=&quot;div_request&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/case&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;case regex=&quot;3&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                     &amp;lt;address  uri=&quot;http://localhost:9001/axis2/services/Subtraction&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/case&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
           &amp;lt;default&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;log level=&quot;full&quot; separator=&quot;,&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;property name=&quot;default_property&quot; value=&quot;Inside Default Case&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/log&amp;gt;    &lt;br/&gt;
           &amp;lt;/default&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/switch&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;send/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/sequence&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/definitions&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An error occurs in the &quot;div_request.xslt &quot; therefore when the sequence executes, and when the error occurs it should call the onError sequence&lt;/p&gt;</description>
